Some residents of the Federal Capital Territory on Monday expressed their views on the just concluded Big Brother Naija Show, ‘’double wahala’’. Big brother Naija is a reality show where 20 contestants (house mates) live together for a period of three months; housemates are evicted each week until a winner emerges. The winner goes home with N25 million cash prize and other benefits. The residents who spoke about the show with our reporter had varied opinions. 